<concept id="concept_spv_xlc_fv">
 <title>MapR FS </title>
 <shortdesc>The MapR FS destination writes files to MapR FS. You can write the data to MapR as flat
        files or Hadoop sequence files. </shortdesc>
 <conbody>
        <p><indexterm>MapR FS
                    destination<indexterm>overview</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>destinations<indexterm>MapR
                    FS</indexterm></indexterm>When you configure a MapR FS destination, <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/D-HM-Overview1"
            /></p>
        <p
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/D-HM-HiveSolutionOverview1"/>
        <p conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/D-HM-Overview2"/>
        <p>The destination can generate events for an event stream. For more information about the
            event framework, see <xref
                href="../Event_Handling/EventFramework-Overview.dita#concept_cph_5h4_lx"/>.</p>
        <p>When necessary, you can enable Kerberos authentication and specify an HDFS user. You can
            also use HDFS configuration files and add other HDFS configuration properties as needed. </p>
        <p conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/D-HM-compression"/>
